## Component Structure
```typescript
// Types/Interfaces at top
interface Props {
  // ...
}

// Named export (not default)
export function ComponentName({ prop1, prop2 }: Props) {
  // 1. Hooks (useAdmin, useCommands, store hooks)
  // 2. State (useState, useRef)
  // 3. Effects (useEffect)
  // 4. Helper functions
  // 5. Render
}
```

## Import Ordering (enforced by Prettier)
1. React/Next.js (`import React`, `import { useCallback }`, `import dynamic from "next/dynamic"`)
2. Third-party (`zustand`, `date-fns`, `react-icons`, `@dnd-kit`)
3. Internal components (`@/components/...`)
4. Types (`@/types/...`)
5. Utilities/hooks/stores (`@/lib/...`, `@/hooks/...`, `@/store/...`)

## Zustand Store Pattern
```typescript
import { create } from "zustand";
import { persist } from "zustand/middleware";

interface StoreState {
  items: Item[];
  setItems: (items: Item[]) => void;
  fetchItems: () => Promise<void>;
}

export const useItemStore = create<StoreState>((set) => ({
  items: [],
  setItems: (items) => set({ items }),
  fetchItems: async () => {
    const res = await fetch("/api/items");
    const data = await res.json();
    set({ items: data });
  },
}));
```
- Stores live in `src/store/`
- Use `persist` middleware for stores that need localStorage
- Keep stores small and focused (atomic pattern)

## SAAS/OSS Dynamic Import Pattern
```typescript
import dynamic from "next/dynamic";

const SettingsContent = dynamic(
  () => import(`./SettingsContent${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_SAAS_FEATURES === "true" ? ".saas" : ".open"}`),
  { ssr: false }
);
```
- `.saas.tsx` for SAAS-only components
- `.open.tsx` for OSS-only components
- No extension for shared components

## UI Components
- Use Shadcn: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- Icons: `react-icons` (import from `react-icons/hi`, `react-icons/fi`, etc.)
- Toast notifications: `sonner`
- Command palette: `cmdk` -- consider adding new features to `src/lib/commands/`
- JSX text: use `&apos;` and `&quot;` instead of literal quotes

## Admin Access
```tsx
// In pages:
const { isAdmin } = useAdmin();
if (!isAdmin) return <AccessDeniedMessage message="Admin access required" />;

// In components:
<AdminOnly fallback={<AccessDeniedMessage />}>
  {/* Admin content */}
</AdminOnly>
```

## FullCalendar Integration
- Calendar component wraps FullCalendar with plugins: dayGridPlugin, timeGridPlugin, multiMonthPlugin, interactionPlugin
- Events come from `useCalendarStore`
- Event handlers dispatch to store actions

## Drag and Drop
- Uses `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable`
- DndProvider wraps draggable areas
- Task reordering and calendar event drag supported
